You are right, it is not possible to make the lines invisible by calling just `polygon.setAttribute()`. The reason is that `setAttribute` is not yet able to subobjects like in `{borders {visible: false}}` and that also the other approach - setting `withLines:false` - fails because the attribute `withLines` is not dynamic. It mainly prevents creation of the lines for efficiency reasons during construction of the polygon. 

We will discuss if we enable these two issues in a future version. 
For the time being, the way to set the lines invisible is the following:

     var ABC = [[0,0], [1,3], [3,2]];
     var poly1=board.create(&#39;polygon&#39;, ABC, {withLines:false});
     var DEF = [[-1,0], [-2,3], [-4,2]];
